node.text:
Learning to give therapeutic treatments can be scary; we often get into our heads and question whether what we are doing is”right”. The thing is, when we allow ourselves to be present and shift our focus to listening, our bodies often know what to do. 

Learning Thai Massage is a part of the AcroYoga curriculum because we believe that taking care of our bodies allows us to have a more sustainable acrobatic practice. Plus, the sensitivity we learn in therapeutics allows us to become better bases and flyers. 

Check out Krishnatakis from @sunshinehouse.gr working this massage with his feet! Anyone else wishing they could be the receiver? 🤚🏼 

Our Greece TT will be held at the magical Sunshine House and we will definitely be participating in some therapeutic goodness!

🐦 ONE WEEK LEFT FOR EARLY BIRD🐦

🇬🇷 Greece Teacher Training with @almuthkramer @aleavolar @johnkarvelis @acroplay and @yogabyjules

September 8-22, 2021 at @sunshinehouse.gr

node.text:
What made you fall in love with AcroYoga?

For many of us, the sense of community and connection are a huge part of why we love the practice.

When we decide to share AcroYoga with others as a teacher, honing the art of co-teaching becomes just as important as learning the skills. Teaching with different people can bring out different parts of you and allows us to constantly learn from others. 

Check out what AYI teachers @almuthkramer and @yogabyjules have to say about AY and co-teaching. If you want to dive into the practice of AcroYoga and the art of co-teaching, join these ladies and an awesome crew in Greece this September for a residential Teacher Training. 

🐦 EARLY BIRD TIL JULY 1st! 🐦

AcroYoga was created by blending yoga, acrobatics and therapeutics to achieve a well rounded practice. While acrobatics builds strength and keeps us playfully flying with friends, therapeutics helps to ground us and to share ways in which to recover from a dynamic practice.⁣
⁣
Healing and recovery balance your acrobatics and support a sustainable, life-long journey with AcroYoga. Also known as a lunar practice, this relaxing and rejuvenating experience includes therapeutic flying, Thai massage, yoga and meditation.⁣

Our new Online Lunar Course is designed for AcroYogis to develop both individual and partner skills and will help to:⁣
⁣
-Cultivate touch, communication, sensitivity, and listening skills⁣
-Increase flexibility and mobility⁣
-Assist in releasing tension and injury recovery⁣

Check out the free preview by clicking the link below. This online course also counts as a pre requisite for our upcoming Teacher Training in Berlin this October!⁣

node.text:
As we all know, the past 18 months have been very unpredictable and all of us have had to adjust to new ways of life. With the ever changing world arena, one constant thing is our need for human connection, and AcroYoga is a great way to get people to communicate and share mutual trust.

Due to travel restrictions, we will only facilitate one Teacher Training this year. Students from various countries will meet for two weeks to dive deep into the art of co-teaching so that they can leave the training ready to share AcroYoga with the world. 

There are still spots available on our Greece TT, which will take place at the beautiful Sunshine House from Septemberr 8-22. We have postponed our Bali TT until December 2022.

If you are being called to take the journey into teaching how to move, connect and play--this is your one chance in 2021!
